L79:## 4. State Machine
L80:
L81:### 4.1 Run State Machine
L82:States:
L83:1. `RUN_CREATED`
L84:2. `PLANNING`
L85:3. `TASKS_READY`
L86:4. `EXECUTING`
L87:5. `MERGING`
L88:6. `COMPLETED`
L89:7. `FAILED`
L90:8. `CANCELLED`
L91:
L92:Transitions:
L93:1. `RUN_CREATED -> PLANNING` when a valid PDR is available and request validation succeeds (see §5.5 and Run creation gating).
L94:2. `PLANNING -> TASKS_READY` when task graph is emitted.
L95:3. `TASKS_READY -> EXECUTING` when at least one task dispatched.
L96:4. `EXECUTING -> MERGING` when merge candidates exist.
L97:5. `MERGING -> EXECUTING` when additional pending tasks remain.
L98:6. `MERGING -> COMPLETED` when all tasks terminal and required merges done.
L99:7. `* -> FAILED` on unrecoverable system error.
L100:8. `* -> CANCELLED` on user/system cancel.
L101:
L102:### 4.2 Task State Machine
L103:States:
L104:1. `TASK_CREATED`
L105:2. `WORKTREE_READY`
L106:3. `PROMPTED`
L107:4. `PATCH_APPLIED`
L108:5. `VERIFYING`
L109:6. `VERIFY_FAILED_RETRYABLE`
L110:7. `VERIFY_PASSED`
L111:8. `MERGE_READY`
L112:9. `MERGED`
L113:10. `REJECTED`
L114:11. `FAILED`
L115:12. `CLEANED`
L116:
L117:Transitions:
L118:1. `TASK_CREATED -> WORKTREE_READY` after successful worktree creation.
L119:2. `WORKTREE_READY -> PROMPTED` after worker receives context.
L120:3. `PROMPTED -> PATCH_APPLIED` when worker outputs patch and patch applies.
L121:4. `PATCH_APPLIED -> VERIFYING` when inspector starts build.
L122:5. `VERIFYING -> VERIFY_FAILED_RETRYABLE` for retryable failures.
L123:6. `VERIFY_FAILED_RETRYABLE -> PROMPTED` while retry_count < max_retries.
L124:7. `VERIFYING -> VERIFY_PASSED` on exit code `0`.
L125:8. `VERIFY_PASSED -> MERGE_READY` when diff and evidence attached.
L126:9. `MERGE_READY -> MERGED` on clean merge.
L127:10. `MERGE_READY -> REJECTED` on mayor policy rejection.
L128:11. `ANY -> FAILED` on non-retryable error.
L129:12. `MERGED|REJECTED|FAILED -> CLEANED` after teardown attempt.
