267:## 6. Task Graph and Scheduling Rules
268:1. A task is runnable only if all `depends_on` tasks are `MERGED`.
269:2. Scheduler must not dispatch two tasks that both edit the same file unless explicitly marked `coeditable=true`.
270:3. Default `max_parallel_tasks` equals `min(OLLAMA_NUM_PARALLEL, 4)`.
271:4. Starvation prevention: oldest runnable task first, then priority.
272:5. Reassignment rule: after task `FAILED`, mayor may create a replacement task only once (`replacement_depth <= 1` in v1).
273:
274:## 7. Worktree Lifecycle Contract
275:1. Create:
276:   1. `git worktree add .tinkertown/task-[id] -b tinkertown/task-[id] main`
277:2. Validate:
278:   1. Worktree path exists and branch points to expected base SHA.
279:3. Use:
280:   1. All worker commands run with cwd set to worktree path.
281:4. Merge:
282:   1. Fast-forward or regular merge only; no rebase in v1 automation.
283:5. Teardown:
284:   1. `git worktree remove .tinkertown/task-[id] --force`
285:   2. `git branch -D tinkertown/task-[id]` after merge/reject/fail.
286:
287:## 8. Safety Guardrails
288:
289:### 8.1 File-System and Command Guardrails
290:1. Worker must be denied access outside assigned worktree root.
291:2. Blocklist destructive commands by default in worker stage:
292:   1. `git reset --hard`
293:   2. `rm -rf /`
294:   3. any command targeting parent paths outside worktree.
295:3. Allowed git cleanup for worker:
296:   1. `git restore --source=HEAD --worktree --staged .` within worktree only.
297:
298:### 8.2 Merge Guardrails
299:1. Reject merge if diff touches files outside task `target_files` unless mayor explicitly expands scope.
300:2. Reject merge if build evidence is stale (older than last commit in worktree).
301:3. Reject merge if unresolved conflict markers exist in patched files.
302:
303:### 8.3 Data Guardrails
304:1. Never store secrets in logs/events.
305:2. Redact values matching configured secret patterns before persistence.
306:
307:## 9. Error Taxonomy and Retry Policy
308:
309:### 9.1 Error Classes
310:1. `E_BUILD_COMPILE`: compile/build failure.
311:2. `E_PATCH_APPLY`: patch failed to apply.
312:3. `E_MERGE_CONFLICT`: merge conflict.
313:4. `E_TOOL_UNAVAILABLE`: missing required binary/tool.
314:5. `E_MODEL_TIMEOUT`: LLM response timeout.
315:6. `E_GUARDRAIL_VIOLATION`: blocked command/path access violation.
316:7. `E_INTERNAL`: unhandled orchestrator exception.
317:
318:### 9.2 Retryability Matrix
319:1. Retryable:
320:   1. `E_BUILD_COMPILE`
321:   2. `E_PATCH_APPLY`
322:   3. `E_MODEL_TIMEOUT`
323:2. Non-retryable (task -> `FAILED`):
324:   1. `E_GUARDRAIL_VIOLATION`
325:   2. `E_TOOL_UNAVAILABLE`
326:3. Conditionally retryable:
327:   1. `E_MERGE_CONFLICT` -> retry once with fresh base and regenerated patch.
328:
329:### 9.3 Retry Limits
330:1. `max_retries_per_task = 3`.
331:2. Backoff schedule: 0s, 3s, 10s.
332:3. Store per-attempt evidence: prompt hash, patch hash, build command, parsed diagnostics.
333:
334:## 10. Verification Contract (Inspector)
335:1. Build command is selected by repo config:
336:   1. SPM module: `swift build`
337:   2. Xcode app: `xcodebuild build -scheme <scheme> -configuration Debug`
338:2. Pass condition: exit code `0`.
339:3. Parse diagnostics from structured outputs when available; regex fallback allowed.
340:4. Preserve raw log file per attempt at:
341:   1. `.tinkertown/runs/<run_id>/tasks/<task_id>/attempt_<n>.log`
342:5. Emit `DiagnosticRecord[]` even when empty.
