371:### 11.3 Status Agent (v1)
372:1. A read-only Status Agent MUST consume `RunRecord`, `TaskRecord[]`, and the metrics in 11.2 to produce a concise, human-readable summary of run progress.
373:2. The Status Agent MUST NOT issue new plans or patches; it only reflects persisted state (no feedback loop into the Mayor/Tinker).
374:3. The CLI `tinkertown summary <run_id>` MUST be backed by the Status Agent and print:
375:   1. Overall metrics for the run.
376:   2. One checklist-style line per task (state, retries, and title).
